criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

        Veteran patients eligible to participate must have:

          -  A chronic migraine headache ICD-10 diagnosis;

          -  A confirmed frequency of > 7 headache days per month;

          -  A primary complaint of headache

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Veteran patients not eligible to participate include:

          -  Non-Veterans;

          -  Veteran patients without a chronic migraine headache ICD-10 diagnosis;

          -  Veteran patients whose primary complaint is not headache;

          -  Veteran who have a history/diagnosis of traumatic brain injury (TBI)

          -  Veteran patients who have had active treatment for chronic low back pain within the
             last 6 months at the time of the screening in order to ensure that the participant's
             primary pain complaint is headache;

          -  Veteran patients who do not speak English;

          -  Veteran patients who have a current diagnosis of severe cognitive impairment indicated
             by clinical provider, medical chart, or Short Portable Mental Status Questionnaire
             (SPMSQ);

          -  Any patients currently suffering from a disabling psychiatric illness (as noted by a
             clinician);

          -  Veteran patients who have had suicidal ideation or homicidal thoughts within the last
             6 months;

          -  Veteran patients who are deemed by clinicians as unable to participate in this trial;

          -  Veteran patients who are terminally ill (life expectancy of < 12 months as noted by a
             clinician;

          -  Veteran patients who are homeless or live in long-term care, nursing home,
             rehabilitation, or domiciliary services;

          -  Veteran patients who decline to or cannot use the VA Annie App;

          -  Veteran patients who decline to or cannot use MyHealtheVet secure messaging.
